wnMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 16, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nzw1665702745583.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nzw1665702745583.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nzw1665702745583.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nzw1665702745583\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__uniface_license_management_202111\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface makes use of Sentinel  to handle licensing of Uniface products.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__note_w2388ab1b5b1_w2389ab1b5_w2390ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> DLM is only available for\n         existing Uniface Enterprise Edition users. </div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__topic_d43957e1_d43958e1_d43959e1_d43960e1_d43961e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440662e52\">\n Sentinel Licensing\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__p_d66878e1_d66879e1_d66880e1\">When you register with Uniface, you get an <dfn class=\"term\">Entitlement</dfn>, which determines the type of license you can use, and the conditions and permissions associated with it.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29438e1_d29439e1_d29440e1\">For the Community Edition, only\n               standalone cloud-served licenses are used. For more information on how to activate\n               your license for the Community Edition, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zoh1665702745727.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zoh1665702745727.html\" title=\"The Uniface 10 Community Edition is a free version of Uniface that enables new and experienced developers, and others interested in Uniface 10 to explore, learn, and use Uniface 10 to build and test applications.\">Install the Uniface Community Edition</a>. \n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29441e1_d29442e1_d29443e1\">For the Enterprise Edition, there are more licensing options, including standalone\n               licenses, and licenses that are managed by a central license server. For more\n               information about the license types, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zxq1665702745800.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxq1665702745800.html\" title=\"We offer a number of Sentinel license types for Uniface. When registering with Uniface, you are given an Entitlement Certificate that defines the license model, deployment type, as well as the conditions and permissions associated with the license.\">Sentinel License Types</a>. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__p_d66881e1_d66882e1_d66883e1\">Licenses are typically configured during Uniface installation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__p_d66884e1_d66885e1_d66886e1\">The Uniface License Management utility\n               (<span class=\"keyword wintitle\">ulic</span>) is responsible for manually activating and downloading\n            required cloud-served licenses, for checking out licenses, renewing the lease on\n            licenses on a regular basis, and returning licenses. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qgt1690346679212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qgt1690346679212.html\" title=\"The Uniface License Management utility (ulic) is responsible for activating and downloading required Sentinel licenses, for checking out licenses, and renewing the lease on licenses on a regular basis. The licenses themselves are maintained by the Sentinel Cloud Server.\">Uniface License Management Utility (ulic)</a>.\n         </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__p_d66890e1_d66891e1_d66892e1\">You can configure some aspects of licensing, such as\n            notification messages, from within Uniface using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$LICENSE_OPTIONS</span>\n            assignment setting. It also allows you configure the location of license files and\n            servers after installation. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__topic_d43962e1_d43963e1_d43964e1_d43965e1_d43966e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440662e113\">\n License Management for the Enterprise Edition\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__p_d66893e1_d66894e1_d66895e1\">For Sentinel licenses, registered Uniface Enterprise Edition users have access to the Entitlement Management System (EMS) portal where they can download license files, set locking criteria, and more.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__p_d66896e1_d66897e1_d66898e1\">The Sentinel RMS License Manager (also known as the\n            RMS Server) can be used to enforce and manage licensing in a multi-user environment.\n            Registered users of the Enterprise Edition can download it under the name <dfn class=\"term\">Uniface\n               RMS</dfn> from <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://my.rocketsoftware.com/RocketCommunity#/downloads\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Rocket Community: Downloads</a> and obtain the\n            appropriate Sentinel license by contacting their Uniface representative. For more\n            information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"paz1665702747377.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/paz1665702747377.html\">Sentinel RMS License Manager</a>.\n         </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__topic_d43967e1_d43968e1_d43969e1_d43970e1_d43971e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440662e136\">\n More Information\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__table_d5870e1_d5871e1_d5872e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Sentinel License Types \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29444e1_d29445e1_d29446e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zxq1665702745800.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxq1665702745800.html\" title=\"We offer a number of Sentinel license types for Uniface. When registering with Uniface, you are given an Entitlement Certificate that defines the license model, deployment type, as well as the conditions and permissions associated with the license.\">Sentinel License Types</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29447e1_d29448e1_d29449e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luw1665702745876.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luw1665702745876.html\" title=\"A standalone cloud-served license is used for any Uniface application where the license is locked to a machine, and connects to the Sentinel Cloud Server (SCC) to obtain and periodically renew the lease on the license. This is also referred to as lease mode.\">Standalone Cloud-Served License</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29450e1_d29451e1_d29452e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pwb1665702747018.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pwb1665702747018.html\" title=\"A standalone on-premises served license runs on a single machine and uses a local license file. It is sometimes referred to as a node-locked license. It requires no internet connection.\">Standalone On-Premises Served License</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29453e1_d29454e1_d29455e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tsv1665702747305.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tsv1665702747305.html\">Network Cloud-Served License</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29456e1_d29457e1_d29458e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"clg1665702749160.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clg1665702749160.html\" title=\"A network on-premise served license is a local license file (or license code) that enables a Sentinel RMS License Manager (also called an RMS Server) to run concurrent licenses. Applications connect to the RMS License Manager over the network. No internet connection is required.\">Network On-Premises Served License</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29459e1_d29460e1_d29461e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mgn1665702749383.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mgn1665702749383.html\" title=\"The Cloud License Manager provides concurrent licensing to any device connected to the internet, without the need for an RMS license manager. For a client to be able to successfully get a session from the Cloud License Manager, they will need both a Registration Token and an Authentication Token.\">Cloud License Manager (LM) Entitlement</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           RMS License Manager \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29462e1_d29463e1_d29464e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"paz1665702747377.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/paz1665702747377.html\">Sentinel RMS License Manager</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29465e1_d29466e1_d29467e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bpr1665702748797.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bpr1665702748797.html\" title=\"Commuter licensing allows you to temporarily use a license on a machine or application that is not connected to the network. This is sometimes referred to as borrowing.\">Commuter Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29468e1_d29469e1_d29470e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cmy1665702748727.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cmy1665702748727.html\">Grace Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29471e1_d29472e1_d29473e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qnf1665702747449.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qnf1665702747449.html\" title=\"A redundant RMS License Manager pool allows you to configure backup Sentinel RMS servers as a fail-over in case a license server goes down. When one RMS License Manager goes down, the remaining RMS License Managers are able to take over to prevent downtime and ensure a license can always be checked out by your Uniface application.\">Redundant RMS License Manager Pool</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Configuring Sentinel Licenses \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29474e1_d29475e1_d29476e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ltp1665702745946.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ltp1665702745946.html\" title=\"To configure a standalone cloud-served license, you need to enter your entitlement ID during installation or run the License Activation utility (ulic) after installing Uniface.\">Configuring Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29477e1_d29478e1_d29479e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uif1665702747088.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uif1665702747088.html\" title=\"To configure standalone on-premises licenses, you need to use the EMS portal and use the appropriate utility for your platform to get the locking criteria.\">Configuring Standalone On-Premises Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29480e1_d29481e1_d29482e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"izl1665702748868.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/izl1665702748868.html\" title=\"A network cloud-served license enables a Sentinel RMS License Manager to run concurrent licenses from a network location\">Configuring Network Cloud-Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29483e1_d29484e1_d29485e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mwx1665702749228.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mwx1665702749228.html\" title=\"You are given an Entitlement ID when you register with Uniface, which allows you to access the Sentinel EMS customer portal, where you can lock your license to a specific machine and obtain the actual license file.\">Configuring Network On-Premises Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29486e1_d29487e1_d29488e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kmt1665702749621.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kmt1665702749621.html\" title=\"To configure your Uniface application to connect to a Cloud LM Entitlement, you need to enter your Registration Token during installation or run the Uniface License Management utility (ulic) after installing Uniface. If you are using Cloud LM to license your Uniface Docker image, you can enter the registration token REGTOKEN environment variable when mounting your image.\">Configuring Cloud LM Licenses</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Returning Sentinel Licenses \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29489e1_d29490e1_d29491e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cgp1665702746819.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgp1665702746819.html\" title=\"You may wish to return a standalone cloud-served license on one machine to use it on another machine.\">Returning Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29492e1_d29493e1_d29494e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mko1665702747232.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mko1665702747232.html\" title=\"If you have a standalone on-premises served license that is no longer required, you can return it using the license revocation tool to disable the license file.\">Returning Standalone On-Premises Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29495e1_d29496e1_d29497e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cwt1665702749016.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cwt1665702749016.html\">Returning Network Cloud-Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29498e1_d29499e1_d29500e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qzo1665702749304.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qzo1665702749304.html\" title=\"If you need to return a network on-premises served license that is no longer required, use the Revocation tool, located in the /common/bin directory of your Uniface installation, as well as in the RMS installation package. This is a Java-based tool that can be run on any platform.\">Returning Network On-Premises Served Licenses</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Configuration Settings \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29501e1_d29502e1_d29503e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xna1665702718729.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xna1665702718729.html\" title=\"Set one or more license management options, according to your Sentinel license type.\">$LICENSE_OPTIONS</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           License Management \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29504e1_d29505e1_d29506e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qgt1690346679212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qgt1690346679212.html\" title=\"The Uniface License Management utility (ulic) is responsible for activating and downloading required Sentinel licenses, for checking out licenses, and renewing the lease on licenses on a regular basis. The licenses themselves are maintained by the Sentinel Cloud Server.\">Uniface License Management Utility (ulic)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Windows Instructions \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29507e1_d29508e1_d29509e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cjh1665702747666.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cjh1665702747666.html\" title=\"The Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS) License Manager enforces and manages licenses for Uniface in multi-user environments.\">Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29510e1_d29511e1_d29512e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"frp1665702749898.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/frp1665702749898.html\">Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29513e1_d29514e1_d29515e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dhe1665702749084.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dhe1665702749084.html\">Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29516e1_d29517e1_d29518e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wla1665702747736.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wla1665702747736.html\" title=\"It is possible to install the Sentinel RMS License Manager without user interaction, which may be useful when deploying RMS License Managers to multiple users.\">Silently Installing the RMS License Manager on Windows</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Unix Instructions \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29519e1_d29520e1_d29521e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lcv1665702746747.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lcv1665702746747.html\" title=\"Normally, the Uniface installer automatically configures the Sentinel license environment on Linux. However, if you ran the installer without root privileges, or you choose the manual configuration option for some other reason, you must manually configure license management.\">Manually Configure Sentinel Licenses on Linux</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29522e1_d29523e1_d29524e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fnb1665702748208.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnb1665702748208.html\" title=\"The Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS) License Manager (also known as the RMS Server) enforces and manages licenses for Uniface in multi-user environments.\">Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29525e1_d29526e1_d29527e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qhf1665702748352.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qhf1665702748352.html\" title=\"To start or stop the RMS License Manager, use the following commands.\">Starting and Stopping the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29528e1_d29529e1_d29530e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mjb1665702748492.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mjb1665702748492.html\" title=\"Use the installation script to update or upgrade an older version of the RMS License Manager and the Cloud Plug-in, or to switch license type from a cloud-served license to a license file or license code (or vice versa).\">Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29531e1_d29532e1_d29533e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luh1665702748423.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luh1665702748423.html\" title=\"To uninstall the RMS License Manager, use the uninstall script that was created in the directory you specified during installation. You will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine.\">Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29534e1_d29535e1_d29536e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hjl1665702748279.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hjl1665702748279.html\" title=\"It is possible to install the Sentinel RMS License Manager without user interaction, which may be useful when deploying RMS License Managers to multiple users.\">Silently Installing the RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           iSeries Instructions \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29537e1_d29538e1_d29539e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gqj1665702749974.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gqj1665702749974.html\" title=\"Ensure that your configuration has access to a Sentinel License.\">Configure a Sentinel License on iSeries</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Troubleshooting \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29540e1_d29541e1_d29542e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kdm1665702750049.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdm1665702750049.html\">Troubleshooting Licensing Issues</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29543e1_d29544e1_d29545e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bzp1665702746226.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzp1665702746226.html\">Common License Management Errors</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nzw1665702745583__li_d29546e1_d29547e1_d29548e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"quw1665702750118.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/quw1665702750118.html\" title=\"The following list provides more information about common Sentinel licensing error codes.\">Common Sentinel Error Codes</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fsr1665702745652.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Distributed License Manager (DLM)</a><p>Rocket Uniface makes use of the Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS), but existing Uniface Enterprise Edition users may continue to use the Distributed License Manager (DLM) to handle licensing of Uniface 10.3.03. If no Sentinel license is selected, DLM is used by default in Uniface 10.3.03.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xna1665702718729.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$LICENSE_OPTIONS</a><p>Set one or more license management options, according to your Sentinel license type.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxq1665702745800.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Sentinel License Types</a><p>We offer a number of Sentinel license types for Uniface. When registering with Uniface, you are given an Entitlement Certificate that defines the license model, deployment type, as well as the conditions and permissions associated with the license.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/paz1665702747377.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Sentinel RMS License Manager</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qgt1690346679212.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface License Management Utility (ulic)</a><p>The Uniface License Management utility (ulic) is responsible for activating and downloading required Sentinel licenses, for checking out licenses, and renewing the lease on licenses on a regular basis. The licenses themselves are maintained by the Sentinel Cloud Server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdm1665702750049.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Troubleshooting Licensing Issues</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface License Management Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 16, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface makes use of Sentinel to handle licensing of Uniface products. Note: DLM is only available for existing Uniface Enterprise Edition users. Sentinel Licensing When you register with Uniface, you get an Entitlement , which determines the type of license you can use, and the conditions and permissions associated with it. For the Community Edition, only standalone cloud-served licenses are used. For more information on how to activate your license for the Community Edition, see Install the Uniface Community Edition . For the Enterprise Edition, there are more licensing options, including standalone licenses, and licenses that are managed by a central license server. For more information about the license types, see Sentinel License Types . Licenses are typically configured during Uniface installation. The Uniface License Management utility ( ulic ) is responsible for manually activating and downloading required cloud-served licenses, for checking out licenses, renewing the lease on licenses on a regular basis, and returning licenses. For more information, see Uniface License Management Utility (ulic) . You can configure some aspects of licensing, such as notification messages, from within Uniface using the $LICENSE_OPTIONS assignment setting. It also allows you configure the location of license files and servers after installation. License Management for the Enterprise Edition For Sentinel licenses, registered Uniface Enterprise Edition users have access to the Entitlement Management System (EMS) portal where they can download license files, set locking criteria, and more. The Sentinel RMS License Manager (also known as the RMS Server) can be used to enforce and manage licensing in a multi-user environment. Registered users of the Enterprise Edition can download it under the name Uniface RMS from Rocket Community: Downloads and obtain the appropriate Sentinel license by contacting their Uniface representative. For more information, see Sentinel RMS License Manager . More Information Sentinel License Types Sentinel License Types Standalone Cloud-Served License Standalone On-Premises Served License Network Cloud-Served License Network On-Premises Served License Cloud License Manager (LM) Entitlement RMS License Manager Sentinel RMS License Manager Commuter Licenses Grace Licenses Redundant RMS License Manager Pool Configuring Sentinel Licenses Configuring Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses Configuring Standalone On-Premises Served Licenses Configuring Network Cloud-Served Licenses Configuring Network On-Premises Served Licenses Configuring Cloud LM Licenses Returning Sentinel Licenses Returning Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses Returning Standalone On-Premises Served Licenses Returning Network Cloud-Served Licenses Returning Network On-Premises Served Licenses Configuration Settings $LICENSE_OPTIONS License Management Uniface License Management Utility (ulic) Windows Instructions Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows Silently Installing the RMS License Manager on Windows Unix Instructions Manually Configure Sentinel Licenses on Linux Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux Starting and Stopping the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix Silently Installing the RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux iSeries Instructions Configure a Sentinel License on iSeries Troubleshooting Troubleshooting Licensing Issues Common License Management Errors Common Sentinel Error Codes Related Links Distributed License Manager (DLM) Rocket Uniface makes use of the Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS), but existing Uniface Enterprise Edition users may continue to use the Distributed License Manager (DLM) to handle licensing of Uniface 10.3.03. If no Sentinel license is selected, DLM is used by default in Uniface 10.3.03. $LICENSE_OPTIONS Set one or more license management options, according to your Sentinel license type. Sentinel License Types We offer a number of Sentinel license types for Uniface. When registering with Uniface, you are given an Entitlement Certificate that defines the license model, deployment type, as well as the conditions and permissions associated with the license. Sentinel RMS License Manager Uniface License Management Utility (ulic) The Uniface License Management utility (ulic) is responsible for activating and downloading required Sentinel licenses, for checking out licenses, and renewing the lease on licenses on a regular basis. The licenses themselves are maintained by the Sentinel Cloud Server. Troubleshooting Licensing Issues Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}